# AVError

**Structure**

A structure that defines the errors that framework operations can generate.

## Declaration

```swift
struct AVError
```

## Error domain

- **errorDomain**

## Error codes

- **AVError.Code**: An enumeration that defines the errors that framework operations can generate.
- **airPlayControllerRequiresInternet**: The AirPlay controller requires an internet connection to function.
- **airPlayReceiverRequiresInternet**: The AirPlay receiver requires an internet connection to function.
- **airPlayReceiverTemporarilyUnavailable**: An AirPlay receiver is temporarily unavailable.
- **applicationIsNotAuthorizedToUseDevice**: The user denied this app permission to capture media.
- **applicationIsNotAuthorized**: The app isn’t authorized to play media.
- **autoWhiteBalanceNotLocked**
- **compositionTrackSegmentsNotContiguous**: The composition can’t add the source media because it contains gaps.
- **contentIsNotAuthorized**: The user isn’t authorized to play the media.
- **contentIsProtected**: The app isn’t authorized to open the media.
- **contentIsUnavailable**: The captured content is unavailable.
- **contentKeyRequestCancelled**: The app canceled a request to retrieve a content key.
- **contentNotUpdated**: The system couldn’t update the captured content.
- **createContentKeyRequestFailed**: The app couldn’t create a content key request.
- **decodeFailed**: The system failed to decode the media.
- **decoderNotFound**: The system can’t find a suitable decoder for the media.
- **decoderTemporarilyUnavailable**: A suitable decoder for the media is temporarily available.
- **deviceAlreadyUsedByAnotherSession**: Your app can’t access the device because another session is currently using it.
- **deviceInUseByAnotherApplication**: Your app can’t access the device because another app is currently using it.
- **deviceLockedForConfigurationByAnotherProcess**: Your app can’t change device settings because another process currently controls the device.
- **deviceNotConnected**: You app can’t access the device because it isn’t connected.
- **deviceWasDisconnected**: A previously connected device is no longer accessible.
- **diskFull**: Recording stopped because the disk is full.
- **displayWasDisabled**: Screen capture failed because the display was inactive.
- **encodeFailed**: The system couldn’t encode the media data.
- **encoderNotFound**: The requested encoder isn’t found.
- **encoderTemporarilyUnavailable**: An appropriate encoder isn’t currently available.
- **exportFailed**: The requested export operation failed.
- **externalPlaybackNotSupportedForAsset**: The current asset doesn’t support playback.
- **failedToLoadMediaData**: The system can’t load the requested media data.
- **failedToLoadSampleData**: The system can’t load the requested sample data.
- **failedToParse**: The system can’t parse the media.
- **fileAlreadyExists**: A file with the same name exists at the location and you can’t overwrite it.
- **fileFailedToParse**: The file is corrupt or in an unrecognized format.
- **fileFormatNotRecognized**: The system can’t open the file because it’s in an unrecognized format.
- **fileTypeDoesNotSupportSampleReferences**: The file type doesn’t support sample references.
- **followExternalSyncDeviceTimedOut**
- **formatUnsupported**: The current asset format isn’t supported.
- **incompatibleAsset**: You can’t display the media because the device isn’t capable of playing the content.
- **incorrectlyConfigured**: The system is incorrectly configured for the requested operation.
- **invalidCompositionTrackSegmentDuration**: You can’t add the source media because its duration in the destination is invalid.
- **invalidCompositionTrackSegmentSourceDuration**: You can’t add the source media because it has no duration.
- **invalidCompositionTrackSegmentSourceStartTime**: You can’t add the source media because its start time in the destination is invalid.
- **invalidOutputURLPathExtension**: The path extension of the output URL is invalid.
- **invalidSampleCursor**: An invalid sample cursor produced an error.
- **invalidSourceMedia**: The system couldn’t read the source media.
- **invalidVideoComposition**: You attempted to present an unsupported video composition.
- **malformedDepth**: The depth data isn’t properly structured.
- **maximumDurationReached**: The recording stopped because it reached the file’s maximum duration.
- **maximumFileSizeReached**: The recording stopped because it reached the file’s maximum size.
- **maximumNumberOfSamplesForFileFormatReached**: The recording stopped because it reached the file’s maximum number of samples.
- **maximumStillImageCaptureRequestsExceeded**: Your app can’t take a photo because there are too many unfinished photo capture requests.
- **mediaChanged**: Recording stopped because the format of the source media changed.
- **mediaDiscontinuity**: Recording stopped because there was an interruption in the input media.
- **mediaExtensionConflict**
- **mediaExtensionDisabled**
- **mediaServicesWereReset**: The system couldn’t perform the operation because media services were unavailable.
- **noCompatibleAlternatesForExternalDisplay**: The system found no compatible external displays.
- **noDataCaptured**: The recording failed because the system received no data.
- **noImageAtTime**: No image is available in the media at the indicated time.
- **noLongerPlayable**: The asset is no longer playable.
- **noSmartFramingsEnabled**
- **noSourceTrack**: The asset doesn’t contain a source track.
- **operationCancelled**: The asset handled a request to cancel loading a property value asynchronously.
- **operationInterrupted**: An interruption occurred while performing a reading or writing operation.
- **operationNotAllowed**: The requested operation isn’t allowed.
- **operationNotSupportedForAsset**: Your app attempted to perform an unsupported operation with the asset.
- **operationNotSupportedForPreset**: Your app attempted to perform an unsupported operation for the current preset.
- **outOfMemory**: The operation couldn’t finish because there isn’t enough memory available to process the media.
- **recordingAlreadyInProgress**: Your app attempted to start recording a movie file while an existing recording is underway.
- **referenceForbiddenByReferencePolicy**: The current reference restrictions prevent the system from loading referenced media.
- **rosettaNotInstalled**: The system doesn’t have Rosetta installed and can’t perform the requested operation.
- **sandboxExtensionDenied**: The system denied issuing the sandbox extension.
- **screenCaptureFailed**: An unexpected problem occurred that prevented screen capture.
- **segmentStartedWithNonSyncSample**: The operation attempted to write a new MPEG-4 segment that didn’t start with a sync sample.
- **serverIncorrectlyConfigured**: The configuration of the HTTP server that streams the media resource isn’t correct.
- **sessionConfigurationChanged**: Recording stopped because the configuration of media sources and destinations changed.
- **sessionHardwareCostOverage**: Your app requested too many camera hardware resources.
- **sessionNotRunning**: The recording couldn’t start because the session isn’t running.
- **sessionWasInterrupted**: The recording stopped because the system interrupted the audio session.
- **toneMappingFailed**: The requested tone mapping failed.
- **torchLevelUnavailable**: The specified torch level is valid but currently unavailable, possibly due to overheating.
- **undecodableMediaData**: The system couldn’t decode the media data.
- **unknown**: An unknown error occurred.
- **unsupportedDeviceActiveFormat**: The capture session doesn’t support the camera device’s active format.
- **unsupportedOutputSettings**: Your app requested unsupported output settings.
- **videoCompositorFailed**: The compositor couldn’t composite video frames.
- **deviceIsNotAvailableInBackground**: You attempted to start a capture session in the background, which isn’t allowed in iOS.

## Error properties

- **device**: The capture device in use.
- **device**
- **fileSize**: The asset file size.
- **fileType**: The asset file type.
- **mediaSubtypes**: An array of media subtypes.
- **mediaType**: The asset media type.
- **mediaType**: The media type.
- **persistentTrackID**: The persistent track ID, if the track exists.
- **presentationTimeStamp**: The presentation time stamp.
- **processID**: The process ID.
- **recordingSuccessfullyFinished**: A Boolean value that indicates whether recording finished successfully.
- **time**: The time duration of the error.

## User info keys

- **AVErrorDeviceKey**: The user information key to retrieve the device name.
- **AVErrorDiscontinuityFlagsKey**: The user information key to retrieve discontinuity flags.
- **AVErrorFileSizeKey**: The user information key to retrieve the file size in bytes.
- **AVErrorFileTypeKey**: The user information key to retrieve the file type.
- **AVErrorMediaTypeKey**: The user information key to retrieve the media type.
- **AVErrorMediaSubTypeKey**: The user information key to retrieve the media subtype.
- **AVErrorPersistentTrackIDKey**: The user information key to retrieve the track’s persistent identifier.
- **AVErrorPIDKey**: The user information key to retrieve the process ID value.
- **AVErrorPresentationTimeStampKey**: The user information key to retrieve the presentation time stamp.
- **AVErrorRecordingSuccessfullyFinishedKey**: The user information key to retrieve a Boolean value that indicates whether recording finished successfully.
- **AVErrorTimeKey**: The user information key to retrieve the error time.

## Errors

- **AVFoundationErrorDomain**: The error domain of AVFoundation errors.

## Conforms To

- CustomNSError
- Equatable
- Error
- Hashable
- Sendable
- SendableMetatype
